race.comment: MAH ALI (6) has won just twice in 36 starts but both of those victories came at today's trip. Racing well including a respectable fourth over the mile at Goulburn last start under 59.5kgs. Big weight drop today and gets a gun run from the inside stall. Sure to prove tough to beat. TAVOLO (3) was eight weeks between runs when an eye-catching fourth in open company last time out over 1300m at Canberra. Well in at the weights after Grima's claim and the extra 200m with that last run under the belt looks an ideal scenario. EXCEED PERFECTION (5) appreciated the step up in distance when fourth recently in a 1400m Class 1 at this track. Races well here and has placed at both runs over 1500m at this circuit. Makes plenty of appeal. OUTCAST GIRL (8) returned in good order at Goulburn in a Class 4 three weeks ago. Twice a winner when second-up and the extra furlong is what she needs. DEVILS DAUGHTER (7) is yet to miss the frame in three first-up runs so keep her in mind off a four-month break.
